main event: A bright white object, brighter than a first magnitude star, was observed for about 5 minutes over the Pacific Ocean.
interesting points: The object was located at coordinates 34.42N 163.40.2E, at an approximate altitude of 50 degrees.
The object was observed to be heading south and its movement was visible to the naked eye.
The sky was clear during the sighting.
The report was forwarded to various military and intelligence agencies for further evaluation.
